                </h2>
                <p class="module-desc">Understand the bedrock of the tax system before diving deeper.</p>
                
                <div class="card-grid">
                    
                    <!-- Card 1: Tax Brackets -->
                    <div class="card-scene" data-xp="100" data-id="card1">
                        <div class="warp-card">
                            <div class="glare"></div>
                            <!-- FRONT -->
                            <div class="card-face front">
                                <div class="card-tag">Income Tax</div>
                                <div class="card-icon">📈</div>
                                <h3 class="card-title">The Bracket Enigma</h3>
                                <p class="card-text">"If I enter a higher tax bracket, will my entire income be taxed at that higher rate?"</p>
                                <button class="card-action">Tap to Reveal Truth</button>
                            </div>
                            <!-- BACK -->
                            <div class="card-face back">
                                <h3 class="back-title">False! Progressive Tax</h3>
                                <p class="back-text">The US uses a <strong>progressive tax system</strong>. Only the income that falls <em>within</em> the new bracket is taxed at the higher rate, not your entire income. You never take home less money by earning more!</p>
                                <button class="btn-claim">Mastered! (+100 XP)</button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Card 2: Standard vs Itemized -->
                    <div class="card-scene" data-xp="150" data-id="card2">
                        <div class="warp-card">
                            <div class="glare"></div>
                            <div class="card-face front">
                                <div class="card-tag">Deductions</div>
                                <div class="card-icon">🛡️</div>
                                <h3 class="card-title">Deduction Defender</h3>
                                <p class="card-text">You have $8,000 in deductible expenses, but the Standard Deduction is $13,850. Which should you choose?</p>
                                <button class="card-action">Solve the Dilemma</button>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card-face back">
                                <h3 class="back-title">Take the Standard!</h3>
                                <p class="back-text">Always choose whichever reduces your taxable income more! A <strong>deduction</strong> lowers the income you are taxed on. Since $13,850 > $8,000, standard wins. You do not need to keep receipts for the standard deduction.</p>
                                <button class="btn-claim">Mastered! (+150 XP)</button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- LEVEL 2 MODULE (Initially Locked visually via JS/CSS class) -->
            <section class="module-section" id="module-2">
                <h2 class="module-title" style="color: var(--text-muted);">
                    <span style="background: var(--color-locked); padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 14px;">Level 2</span>
                    Advanced Strategies
                </h2>
                <p class="module-desc">Unlock by gaining 250 XP in Level 1.</p>
                
                <div class="card-grid">
                    
                    <!-- Card 3: Capital Gains (Locked) -->
                    <div class="card-scene locked" data-xp="200" data-id="card3" data-required-xp="250">
                        <div class="warp-card">
                            <div class="glare"></div>
                            <div class="card-face front">
                                <div class="lock-icon">🔒</div>
                                <div class="card-tag">Investments</div>
                                <div class="card-icon">🏛️</div>
                                <h3 class="card-title">Capital Gains Guru</h3>
                                <p class="card-text">You bought a stock and it grew 50%. You sell it after 11 months. Good idea?</p>
                                <button class="card-action">Requires Level 2</button>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card-face back">
                                <h3 class="back-title">Wait 1 More Month!</h3>
                                <p class="back-text">Selling before 1 year triggers <strong>Short-Term Capital Gains</strong> (taxed like normal income, up to 37%). Waiting 1+ year triggers <strong>Long-Term Capital Gains</strong> (taxed at 0%, 15%, or 20%). Patience pays!</p>
                                <button class="btn-claim">Mastered! (+200 XP)</button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Card 4: Credits vs Deductions (Locked) -->
                    <div class="card-scene locked" data-xp="250" data-id="card4" data-required-xp="250">
                        <div class="warp-card">
                            <div class="glare"></div>
                            <div class="card-face front">
                                <div class="lock-icon">🔒</div>
                                <div class="card-tag">Tax Credits</div>
                                <div class="card-icon">💎</div>
                                <h3 class="card-title">Credit Crusader</h3>
                                <p class="card-text">Which is better: A $1,000 Tax Deduction or a $1,000 Tax Credit?</p>
                                <button class="card-action">Requires Level 2</button>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card-face back">
                                <h3 class="back-title">Tax Credit Wins!</h3>
                                <p class="back-text">A <strong>Deduction</strong> lowers your taxable income (saving you a percentage based on your bracket). A <strong>Credit</strong> is a dollar-for-dollar reduction of the actual tax you owe. $1k credit = $1k more in your pocket!</p>
                                <button class="btn-claim">Mastered! (+250 XP)</button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </section>

             <!-- LEVEL 3 MODULE -->
             <section class="module-section" id="module-3">
                <h2 class="module-title" style="color: var(--text-muted);">
                    <span style="background: var(--color-locked); padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 14px;">Level 3</span>
                    The Final Bosses
                </h2>
                <p class="module-desc">Unlock by gaining 700 XP.</p>
                
                <div class="card-grid">
                    
                    <!-- Card 5: W2 vs 1099 -->
                    <div class="card-scene locked" data-xp="150" data-id="card5" data-required-xp="700">
                        <div class="warp-card">
                            <div class="glare"></div>
                            <div class="card-face front">
                                <div class="lock-icon">🔒</div>
                                <div class="card-tag">Employment</div>
                                <div class="card-icon">⚔️</div>
                                <h3 class="card-title">W-2 vs 1099 Battle</h3>
                                <p class="card-text">As a freelancer (1099), why is your tax bill suddenly so high at the end of the year?</p>
                                <button class="card-action">Requires Level 3</button>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card-face back">
                                <h3 class="back-title">Self-Employment Tax!</h3>
                                <p class="back-text">W-2 employees split payroll taxes (FICA) with their employer. As a 1099 contractor, you are both employee and employer! You must pay the full 15.3% <strong>Self-Employment Tax</strong>. Keep track of write-offs!</p>
                                <button class="btn-claim">Mastered! (+150 XP)</button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Card 6: Depreciation -->
                    <div class="card-scene locked" data-xp="150" data-id="card6" data-required-xp="700">
                        <div class="warp-card">
                            <div class="glare"></div>
                            <div class="card-face front">
                                <div class="lock-icon">🔒</div>
                                <div class="card-tag">Business Assets</div>
                                <div class="card-icon">🏚️</div>
                                <h3 class="card-title">Phantom Expense</h3>
                                <p class="card-text">You bought a heavy duty truck for your business. Can you deduct the entire cost today?</p>
                                <button class="card-action">Requires Level 3</button>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card-face back">
                                <h3 class="back-title">Hello, Depreciation!</h3>
                                <p class="back-text">Normally, large assets must be <strong>depreciated</strong> (deducted slowly over several years). However, loopholes like Section 179 or Bonus Depreciation sometimes allow you to deduct the entire purchase price in year 1!</p>
                                <button class="btn-claim">Mastered! (+150 XP)</button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </section>

        </div>
    </main>
</div>

<script>
    /**
     * ==========================================================================
     * TAXMASTER - INTERACTIVITY & GAMIFICATION LOGIC
     * ==========================================================================
     * Handles 3D Warp effect, Card Flipping, XP Management, and Unlocks.
     */

    document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
        
        // --- State Management ---
        const state = {
            xp: 0,
            maxXP: 1000,
            level: 1,
            conceptsMastered: 0,
            totalConcepts: 6,
            masteredCards: new Set()
        };

        // --- DOM Elements ---
        const cards = document.querySelectorAll('.card-scene');
        const xpDisplay = document.getElementById('xp-display');
        const xpProgress = document.getElementById('xp-progress');
        const conceptsDisplay = document.getElementById('concepts-display');
        const levelBadges = document.querySelectorAll('.level-badge, #sidebar-level');

        // --- 1. 3D WARP ANIMATION LOGIC ---
        // We apply a transform: rotateX and rotateY based on cursor position relative to card center.
        cards.forEach(card => {
            const warpWrapper = card.querySelector('.warp-card');
            const glare = card.querySelector('.glare');
            let bounds;

            // Mouse Enter - initialize tracking
            card.addEventListener('mouseenter', () => {
                // If card is locked, disable 3D effect
                if(card.classList.contains('locked')) return;
                
                bounds = card.getBoundingClientRect();
                card.classList.remove('leave');
            });

            // Mouse Move - apply math for warp
            card.addEventListener('mousemove', (e) => {
                if(card.classList.contains('locked')) return;
                
                if (!bounds) bounds = card.getBoundingClientRect();
                
                const mouseX = e.clientX;
                const mouseY = e.clientY;
                const leftX = mouseX - bounds.x;
                const topY = mouseY - bounds.y;
                const center = {
                    x: leftX - bounds.width / 2,
                    y: topY - bounds.height / 2
                };
                
                // Rotation intensity (lower is more intense, higher is subtle)
                const distance = Math.sqrt(center.x ** 2 + center.y ** 2);
                
                // Notion style prefers subtle animations, limit the max rotation
                const maxRotation = 12; // degrees
                const rotateX = (center.y / (bounds.height / 2)) * -maxRotation;
                const rotateY = (center.x / (bounds.width / 2)) * maxRotation;
                
                // If card is flipped, reverse the Y rotation to feel natural
                const isFlipped = card.classList.contains('is-flipped');
                const finalRotateY = isFlipped ? rotateY + 180 : rotateY;

                // Scale up slightly on hover
                const scale = isFlipped ? 1.05 : 1.02;

                // Apply transform
                warpWrapper.style.transform = `
                    rotateX(${rotateX}deg) 
                    rotateY(${finalRotateY}deg) 
                    scale3d(${scale}, ${scale}, ${scale})
                `;

                // Move glare
                if (glare) {
                    const angle = Math.atan2(center.y, center.x) * 180 / Math.PI - 90;
                    glare.style.background = `linear-gradient(${angle}deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.4) 0%, rgba(255,255,255,0) 80%)`;
                }
            });

            // Mouse Leave - reset to idle
            card.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => {
                if(card.classList.contains('locked')) return;
                
                card.classList.add('leave');
                bounds = null;
                
                // Reset transform but respect flip state
                const isFlipped = card.classList.contains('is-flipped');
                if (isFlipped) {
                    warpWrapper.style.transform = `rotateY(180deg) scale3d(1, 1, 1)`;
                } else {
                    warpWrapper.style.transform = `rotateX(0deg) rotateY(0deg) scale3d(1, 1, 1)`;
                }
            });

            // --- 2. CARD FLIPPING LOGIC ---
            card.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
                // Ignore if locked or clicking the claim button
                if(card.classList.contains('locked')) {
                    shakeElement(card); // Feedback that it's locked
                    return;
                }
                
                if(e.target.classList.contains('btn-claim')) return;

                // Toggle flip
                const isFlipped = card.classList.toggle('is-flipped');
                
                // Force a reset of bounds to fix orientation glitch mid-flip
                bounds = card.getBoundingClientRect();
                
                if (!isFlipped) {
                    warpWrapper.style.transform = `rotateX(0deg) rotateY(0deg) scale3d(1, 1, 1)`;
                } else {
                    warpWrapper.style.transform = `rotateY(180deg) scale3d(1.05, 1.05, 1.05)`;
                }
            });

            // --- 3. GAMIFICATION LOGIC (CLAIM XP) ---
            const btnClaim = card.querySelector('.btn-claim');
            if (btnClaim) {
                btnClaim.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
                    e.stopPropagation(); // Prevent card flip
                    const cardId = card.getAttribute('data-id');
                    
                    if (state.masteredCards.has(cardId)) return; // Already claimed

                    const xpVal = parseInt(card.getAttribute('data-xp'), 10);
                    
                    // Update State
                    state.xp += xpVal;
                    state.conceptsMastered += 1;
                    state.masteredCards.add(cardId);

                    // Update UI
                    updateDashboard();
                    checkLevelUps();
                    
                    // Button UI Change
                    btnClaim.classList.add('claimed');
                    btnClaim.innerHTML = `✓ Claimed`;
                    
                    // Celebration Particle Effect
                    createConfetti(e.clientX, e.clientY);
                    
                    // Optionally unflip card after short delay
                    setTimeout(() => {
                        card.classList.remove('is-flipped');
                        warpWrapper.style.transform = `rotateX(0deg) rotateY(0deg) scale3d(1, 1, 1)`;
                    }, 1500);
                });
            }
        });

        // --- Core Application Functions ---

        function updateDashboard() {
            // Update Text
            xpDisplay.innerHTML = `${state.xp} <span>/ ${state.maxXP} XP</span>`;
            conceptsDisplay.innerText = state.conceptsMastered;
            
            // Animate Progress Bar
            const percentage = Math.min((state.xp / state.maxXP) * 100, 100);
            xpProgress.style.width = `${percentage}%`;
        }

        function checkLevelUps() {
            let newLevel = 1;
            if (state.xp >= 700) newLevel = 3;
            else if (state.xp >= 250) newLevel = 2;

            if (newLevel > state.level) {
                state.level = newLevel;
                
                // Update Badges
                levelBadges.forEach(badge => {
                    if (badge.id === 'sidebar-level') {
                        badge.innerText = state.level;
                    } else {
                        badge.innerText = `Level ${state.level}`;
                        // Trigger pulse animation restart
                        badge.style.animation = 'none';
                        void badge.offsetWidth; 
                        badge.style.animation = 'pulse 2s infinite';
                    }
                });

                // Heavy Confetti for Level Up
                for(let i=0; i<30; i++) {
                    setTimeout(() => createConfetti(window.innerWidth/2, window.innerHeight/2, true), i * 50);
                }
            }

            // Unlock Cards
            cards.forEach(card => {
                if (card.classList.contains('locked')) {
                    const reqXp = parseInt(card.getAttribute('data-required-xp'), 10);
                    if (state.xp >= reqXp) {
                        unlockCard(card);
                    }
                }
            });
        }

        function unlockCard(card) {
            // Visual transition for unlocking
            card.classList.remove('locked');
            
            const frontFace = card.querySelector('.card-face.front');
            const lockIcon = card.querySelector('.lock-icon');
            const actionBtn = card.querySelector('.card-action');
            const header = card.closest('section').querySelector('.module-title span');
            
            // Remove Lock
            if (lockIcon) {
                lockIcon.style.transform = 'translate(-50%, -50%) scale(0)';
                lockIcon.style.opacity = '0';
                setTimeout(() => lockIcon.remove(), 300);
            }
            
            // Update UI elements from locked state
            actionBtn.innerText = "Tap to Reveal Truth";
            
            // If header exists and still shows locked color, update it
            if (header && header.style.background.includes('var(--color-locked)')) {
                header.style.background = 'var(--bg-hover-dark)';
                header.style.color = 'var(--text-main)';
                header.parentElement.style.color = 'var(--text-main)';
                const desc = header.parentElement.nextElementSibling;
                if (desc) desc.innerText = "Module Unlocked! Dive in.";
            }

            // Pop Animation
            card.style.animation = 'popIn 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1) forwards';
        }

        // --- Utility Functions ---

        function shakeElement(el) {
            el.animate([
                { transform: 'translateX(0)' },
                { transform: 'translateX(-5px)' },
                { transform: 'translateX(5px)' },
                { transform: 'translateX(-5px)' },
                { transform: 'translateX(5px)' },
                { transform: 'translateX(0)' }
            ], {
                duration: 300,
                iterations: 1
            });
        }

        function createConfetti(x, y, isLevelUp = false) {
            const colors = ['#0f7b6c', '#eb5757', '#f2c94c', '#2d9cdb'];
            for (let i = 0; i < (isLevelUp ? 5 : 10); i++) {
                const particle = document.createElement('div');
                particle.classList.add('confetti');
                
                // Randomize properties
                const color = colors[Math.floor(Math.random() * colors.length)];
                const size = Math.random() * 8 + 4;
                const spreadX = (Math.random() - 0.5) * (isLevelUp ? window.innerWidth : 300);
                
                particle.style.background = color;
                particle.style.width = `${size}px`;
                particle.style.height = `${size}px`;
                
                // Position at click/center
                particle.style.left = `${x}px`;
                particle.style.top = `${y}px`;
                
                // Custom CSS variables for animation path
                particle.style.setProperty('--tx', `${spreadX}px`);
                
                document.body.appendChild(particle);
                
                // Add custom dynamic animation
                particle.animate([
                    { transform: `translate(0, 0) rotate(0deg) scale(1)`, opacity: 1 },
                    { transform: `translate(${spreadX}px, -100px) rotate(180deg) scale(1.2)`, opacity: 1, offset: 0.2 },
                    { transform: `translate(${spreadX * 1.5}px, ${window.innerHeight}px) rotate(720deg) scale(0)`, opacity: 0 }
                ], {
                    duration: Math.random() * 1000 + 1500,
                    easing: 'cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94)',
                    fill: 'forwards'
                });

                // Cleanup
                setTimeout(() => {
                    particle.remove();
                }, 2500);
            }
        }
        
        // Initial setup for Dashboard
        updateDashboard();
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
